Tair Narynov - Founder of STEM Central Asia

This is the official website of Tair Narynov, founder and Global Director of STEM Central Asia.

Tair Narynov is a 4.0 GPA student at High Bluff Academy in San Diego, California.

Tair Narynov is a research intern at the University of California, San Diego (UCSD).

Tair Narynov competes in FIRST Robotics with team MarauderTech 9573.

Tair Narynov won the Bishops SWEN Knights Hackathon sponsored by Lockheed Martin.

Tair Narynov serves as the President of the Model United Nations Club.

Tair Narynov is active in the Associated Student Body (ASB).

Tair Narynov led a team in the Aerospace Robotics Coding Competition.
